<appendix id="installation">
<title>Installation</title>

<sect1 id="getting-kfilereplace">
<title>How to install &kfilereplace;</title>
<para>
&kfilereplace; is actually part of Kdewebdev tool, so in order to install it, you must obtain a copy of Kdewebdev. Note that if you are using a KDE installation provided by your OS vendor, probably you already have Kdewebdev installed, in this case you can use &kfilereplace; either by opening Quanta plus web editor or by calling it directly(unless you have an old KDE version). If not you can download Kdewebdev package from the internet, please refer to <ulink url="http://kdewebdev.org">Kdewebdev home site</ulink> for more informations.
<!--&install.intro.documentation;-->
</para>
<para>http://kde-apps.org
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="requirements">
 <title>Requirements</title>
  <para>
    In order to use the command <link linkend="available-commands">[$mathexp:some_math_expression$]</link> you should install the bc mathematical utility (version 1.06 or newer) written by Philip A. Nelson(philnelson@acm.org).
  </para>

</sect1>

</appendix>

